WEBVTT

00:30.947 --> 00:34.868
<i>The longer you're in the game,</i>
<i>the more you know what really matters.</i>

00:38.246 --> 00:40.582
<i>Lone wolves don't get far.</i>

00:42.959 --> 00:44.252
<i>You need a crew.</i>

00:52.552 --> 00:54.804
<i>You got to figure out who you can trust.</i>

00:59.809 --> 01:01.936
<i>'Cause there's two sides to every story.</i>

01:11.988 --> 01:14.657
<i>And neither one's really the truth.</i>

01:19.871 --> 01:22.165
-It's okay…
-I'm so sorry.

01:22.248 --> 01:24.459
-Dickens.
-Yeah.

01:24.542 --> 01:26.586
<i>It's hard to know</i>
<i>who deserves your loyalty.</i>

01:26.669 --> 01:29.214
-I'm Kate.
-Laura.

01:38.181 --> 01:39.140
<i>If you're lucky,</i>

01:39.224 --> 01:43.186
<i>you'll find someone else</i>
<i>who sees the world like you see it…</i>

02:02.288 --> 02:05.792
<i>…who wants the same things</i>
<i>in the same ways.</i>

02:15.260 --> 02:16.261
<i>You're a team.</i>

02:19.472 --> 02:21.641
<i>The both of you against the world.</i>

02:38.825 --> 02:39.826
<i>Or so you think.</i>

02:43.329 --> 02:44.539
Have a good one.

02:57.385 --> 02:59.929
<i>Because trust can be earned.</i>

03:01.681 --> 03:02.891
<i>It can be given…</i>

03:12.233 --> 03:14.944
<i>-and it can be stolen.</i>

03:35.131 --> 03:36.424
<i>And once it's gone…</i>

03:37.050 --> 03:38.801
<i>You have reached a number</i>

03:38.885 --> 03:41.554
<i>that has been disconnected</i>
<i>or is no longer in service.</i>

03:47.227 --> 03:50.146
<i>…it's gone forever.</i>

04:03.368 --> 04:04.869
Took as much as I could carry.

04:05.370 --> 04:08.581
If I were stronger, you'd be poorer.

04:09.207 --> 04:11.542
That is about $2 million.

04:12.710 --> 04:14.254
My associate took it from your box

04:14.337 --> 04:16.464
at the Dunne & Company vault
nine days ago.

04:17.340 --> 04:18.883
Did you even know it was gone?

04:20.551 --> 04:23.221
I don't believe we did, no.

04:23.304 --> 04:27.183
You asked me
to evaluate my competitors' security.

04:28.476 --> 04:29.602
I've found it wanting.

04:29.686 --> 04:30.770
Mmm.

04:30.853 --> 04:32.522
And you recommend…

04:32.605 --> 04:36.442
Uh, you and your partners
have specific needs,

04:36.526 --> 04:38.861
a diverse portfolio,

04:38.945 --> 04:41.489
best kept in a certain amount of shadow,

04:41.572 --> 04:45.785
physical assets in danger of theft,
but also at the mercy of the elements,

04:45.868 --> 04:50.707
I would suggest your only real shot
at security and privacy

04:50.790 --> 04:54.085
is the vault that I have built
and perfected here at SLS.

04:54.168 --> 04:55.920
Hmm.

04:56.004 --> 04:58.715
See, Aldritch Dunne is a personal friend.

04:59.924 --> 05:01.926
I've been banking there for 30 years.

05:02.010 --> 05:04.554
-Hmm.
-Loyalty is worthless.

05:04.637 --> 05:05.680
Faith is dead.

05:07.098 --> 05:09.475
At the end of the day,
all it comes down to

05:09.559 --> 05:12.687
is you versus the people
who want what you have.

05:14.063 --> 05:15.815
And the only thing that matters is,

05:16.691 --> 05:21.029
can you manipulate them
better than they manipulate you?

05:57.523 --> 05:59.650
<i>Only way to pull off the impossible?</i>

06:01.235 --> 06:02.904
<i>Crew up with people you trust.</i>

06:13.581 --> 06:16.876
<i>Or at least trust to do it right.</i>

06:32.100 --> 06:36.354
Stan!
Your parrot shit in the kitchen again.

06:36.437 --> 06:38.689
It's not mine.
And it's not a parrot, Barbara.

06:38.773 --> 06:41.317
It's an ariel toucan.
Fifty left in the world.

06:41.401 --> 06:44.737
Why's he got to be in the kitchen?
I got my leggings party at 6:00.

06:44.821 --> 06:46.697
I'm trading the bird
to a guy in Williamsburg

06:46.781 --> 06:48.533
for a case of Cheval Blanc '47,

06:48.616 --> 06:51.953
which I'm going to trade for a Lotus
from that dentist. That's why.

06:52.036 --> 06:55.665
Stan. Stan. I got my eye doctor
appointment at 3:00.

06:55.748 --> 06:57.417
-I'll take you.
-What's a Lotus?

06:57.500 --> 06:59.085
-Last time we were late.
-It's a car.

06:59.168 --> 07:02.422
-Ma, don't come down. We got hours.
-A car? Why do you need a car?

07:02.505 --> 07:06.259
-Doctor don't like it when I'm late!
-It's for a friend! You'll be on time!

07:06.342 --> 07:07.760
Oh. Uh…

07:07.844 --> 07:10.930
Super. Not a fan of the yelling.

07:12.557 --> 07:14.809
Your parrot's going
in the meat grinder, Stan.

07:16.185 --> 07:17.437
The meat grinder.

07:18.354 --> 07:20.940
One, you better check your tone
when you talk to me.

07:21.023 --> 07:23.234
Two, you are definitely
cleaning up this bird shit.

07:23.317 --> 07:25.653
And three,
you're sleeping on the couch, Stan!

07:25.736 --> 07:27.655
-You're sleeping on the couch!

07:27.738 --> 07:28.781
I love you!

07:34.287 --> 07:37.540
Mr. Rossi, Mr. Rossi,
always kind and never bossy.

07:37.623 --> 07:39.292
Got that little item for you.

07:40.668 --> 07:45.756
Now, as far as customs knows,
this is parmesan.

07:46.340 --> 07:49.135
Not into larvae myself,
but to each his own.

07:49.802 --> 07:51.971
You need anything else,
I'm your guy, okay?

07:52.054 --> 07:53.514
-Thank you.
-Thanks, Stan.

07:59.562 --> 08:01.731
How about a kilo of magic mushrooms?

08:01.814 --> 08:03.399
Depends on how long I got to grow 'em.

08:03.483 --> 08:04.400
Two to five.

08:05.776 --> 08:07.153
Time off for good behavior.

08:10.323 --> 08:11.449
C'mere, you fuck.

08:11.532 --> 08:12.700
-Oh!

08:13.701 --> 08:16.412
Ah, what's up, boss? Oh, man.

08:17.038 --> 08:18.831
-How you doing?
-I'm still here.

08:18.915 --> 08:19.999
-You all right?
-Yeah.

08:25.296 --> 08:26.297
So what's the score?

08:26.380 --> 08:30.051
Why's it gotta be about a score?
Maybe I came in for a ribeye.

08:30.134 --> 08:31.552
I'm retired, Leo.

08:33.346 --> 08:36.766
Ma's a mess
and Barbara's on me like a hawk.

08:36.849 --> 08:38.059
Don't get me wrong, man,

08:38.142 --> 08:41.812
I would love nothing more than to
bow out of this shitshow and mix it up,

08:41.896 --> 08:46.234
but whatever you're cooking,
I got to respectfully decline.

08:48.945 --> 08:51.906
Seven billion dollars. Give or take.

09:05.294 --> 09:06.671
So the vault's underground?

09:06.754 --> 09:10.967
Yeah, deep,
cased in steel-reinforced concrete.

09:11.050 --> 09:14.887
That's fun.
You drill through the door?

09:14.971 --> 09:18.558
Three doors, cobalt-plated.
That's just the appetizer.

09:18.641 --> 09:20.268
-Bring on the main, baby.
-Yeah, right.

09:20.351 --> 09:24.105
To even approach the door,
you got to get into a secure subfloor,

09:25.106 --> 09:29.777
past biometric sensors
laid into an uninterruptible power supply,

09:30.570 --> 09:33.447
linked to security teams
with military training,

09:33.531 --> 09:38.536
who are armed, willing,
and ready to use deadly force.

09:38.619 --> 09:40.746
Still waiting for the punchline here, man.

09:41.956 --> 09:43.165
The Triplets.

09:43.249 --> 09:46.210
Oh, you mean the, uh,
the arson brothers from Block D?

09:46.294 --> 09:48.796
Oh, damn, I forgot about those guys.

09:48.879 --> 09:50.840
-Crazy motherfuckers.

09:50.923 --> 09:54.427
Nah. No, The Triplets
are a different breed of criminal.

09:55.303 --> 09:56.596
<i>Cho-Young Woo,</i>

09:57.513 --> 10:01.267
<i>lead shareholder of Jongo,</i>
<i>Korea's biggest private bank.</i>

10:02.268 --> 10:06.731
<i>They say he's Kim Jong-Un's</i>
<i>nephew or cousin.</i>

10:06.814 --> 10:08.024
<i>Nobody really asks.</i>

10:09.317 --> 10:12.737
<i>Suzanne Grosvenor,</i>
<i>Lead Banker at Duncan-Welsh.</i>

10:13.988 --> 10:16.324
<i>Word is the Queen's got her on speed dial.</i>

10:17.617 --> 10:20.536
<i>And Stefan Thiele,</i>

10:21.454 --> 10:23.789
<i>Swiss CEO of Banque Brünner,</i>

10:23.873 --> 10:26.751
<i>started by</i>
<i>his great-great-grandfather in 1898.</i>

10:26.834 --> 10:31.005
<i>Let's just say that their gold</i>
<i>might still have a swastika or two on it.</i>

10:32.340 --> 10:36.510
<i>Between them,</i>
<i>they control half a trillion dollars.</i>

10:37.845 --> 10:39.639
Most of their money's in Europe.

10:40.514 --> 10:41.849
But a few years back,

10:42.683 --> 10:46.187
they took control of a fortune
in unsecured bearer bonds.

10:47.188 --> 10:48.481
Like the <i>Die Hard</i> thing?

10:48.564 --> 10:50.733
Yeah. The <i>Die Hard</i> thing.

10:51.442 --> 10:54.320
With unsecured bonds,
you can't track who owns them.

10:54.403 --> 10:57.740
Which is why people used to use them
for all sorts of illegal shit.

10:57.823 --> 11:02.495
So in 1982, the US government
stepped in and said,

11:02.578 --> 11:04.664
"All bonds got to be registered."

11:04.747 --> 11:09.043
But the pre-'82 bonds that are
still stranded out there in the wild,

11:09.794 --> 11:13.631
they can still be cashed in,
and that is what The Triplets have.

11:14.965 --> 11:17.802
About $7 billion worth.

11:18.678 --> 11:20.554
And they're all down in that vault?

11:20.638 --> 11:22.765
Not yet. They're coming in from Europe.

11:22.848 --> 11:26.894
The Triplets made a deal with the guy
who owns the vault to put them down there.

11:26.977 --> 11:32.566
He guarantees that it's weatherproof,
shockproof, and thief-proof.

11:34.819 --> 11:35.653
Yeah.

11:36.362 --> 11:38.531
In a couple of months,
we're gonna break in,

11:38.614 --> 11:40.658
and take him for everything he's got.

11:41.617 --> 11:42.535
Who's the mark?

11:43.661 --> 11:45.162
<i>Roger Salas.</i>

11:49.333 --> 11:50.167
Okay.

11:52.336 --> 11:53.838
Settle down, everyone.

11:54.588 --> 11:56.924
So it's a big win for the team.

11:57.508 --> 11:58.801
Let's hear it for Hannah,

11:58.884 --> 12:01.846
who did some,
uh, pretty special work for us.

12:02.513 --> 12:06.684
Now, we keep The Triplets happy,
the rest of the town falls into line.

12:06.767 --> 12:08.728
-Screw it up, we're working at Panera.

12:08.811 --> 12:12.356
Carlos will do Level 4 background checks
on all key personnel.

12:12.440 --> 12:16.235
Andrew's team will handle audits
of security protocols.

12:16.318 --> 12:18.195
Anything feels amiss, you come to me.

12:18.279 --> 12:20.281
This is rubber meets the road.

12:20.364 --> 12:21.991
Either we rise or we fall.

12:22.074 --> 12:23.159
Guys.

12:24.243 --> 12:25.619
Hannah, take app vulnerability.

12:25.703 --> 12:28.330
-Rajiv, source code review.
-Piece of cake, boss man.

12:29.415 --> 12:30.458
<i>What do you think?</i>

12:30.541 --> 12:32.001
<i>It's still impossible.</i>

12:32.710 --> 12:35.463
<i>I mean, maybe with somebody</i>
<i>on the inside. Maybe.</i>

12:36.046 --> 12:37.673
Let's assume I got that covered.

12:39.467 --> 12:41.051
Can you source the gear?

12:41.135 --> 12:43.888
Job like this comes to what, like…

12:45.514 --> 12:47.266
half a million in seed money?

12:47.892 --> 12:48.726
You pull that?

12:48.809 --> 12:52.521
Yeah. I got a guy who works security
for OTB in Garden City.

12:52.605 --> 12:54.356
We cut him in,
he'll make it an easy score.

12:54.440 --> 12:56.817
-So we do a job to do a job.
-Yeah.

13:00.946 --> 13:03.282
Not for nothing, man, but…

13:04.742 --> 13:09.705
You never cared about cars,
or yachts, or whatever.

13:11.207 --> 13:12.416
Why chance it?

13:13.209 --> 13:16.378
Are you confused by a billion dollars?

13:16.462 --> 13:18.130
Big win is a big risk.

13:18.714 --> 13:22.468
We got a chance to fix everything
that ever went wrong in our lives.

13:22.551 --> 13:26.430
Look, the way I see it,
all it takes is you, me, a driver,

13:27.097 --> 13:31.310
a forger, security, and maybe a chemist.

13:50.329 --> 13:53.374
If you could, just pick the one
you saw run out of the depot.

13:53.457 --> 13:55.668
I mean, that's a little tricky.

13:55.751 --> 13:59.338
They're all sort of equally flea-ridden,
you know?

13:59.421 --> 14:00.631
Um…

14:00.714 --> 14:02.633
Though I did hear him speak,

14:02.716 --> 14:04.301
Um, I believe he said,

14:04.385 --> 14:06.637
you'll have to excuse my French, um,

14:06.720 --> 14:08.472
"I'm a fucking moron."

14:09.181 --> 14:12.059
Perhaps you could instruct the gentlemen
to say that and I could…

14:14.937 --> 14:18.148
We're going to have you all say,
"I'm a fucking moron."

14:18.232 --> 14:20.359
-Number one?
-Thank you.

14:21.026 --> 14:22.444
I'm a fucking moron.

14:26.699 --> 14:27.575
Number two.

14:28.617 --> 14:30.703
I'm a moron. Fucking moron.

14:32.288 --> 14:33.831
No. Maybe the next one?

14:35.833 --> 14:37.042
Number three?

14:38.085 --> 14:39.086
I'm a fucking moron.

14:39.169 --> 14:42.047
Oh, that was a little fast,
wasn't it? Uh, may I?

14:42.923 --> 14:46.802
Number three, I'd love to really hear you
sell the idiocy.

14:46.886 --> 14:48.596
I want to know that you understand

14:48.679 --> 14:50.598
how irretrievably stupid it was of you

14:50.681 --> 14:53.017
to try to rob a FedEx depot
in broad daylight,

14:53.100 --> 14:56.061
that you should've listened to anyone
who tried to stop you

14:56.145 --> 14:58.272
and that you recognize your own ineptitude

14:58.355 --> 15:01.525
in a deep, meaningful, spiritual way.

15:09.033 --> 15:13.329
I am a fucking moron.

15:17.124 --> 15:19.293
No. Um, number four?

15:21.921 --> 15:22.755
Number four?

15:24.506 --> 15:27.051
I am a fucking moron.

15:33.349 --> 15:36.602
Maybe less
of a fucking idiot next time? Yeah?

15:36.685 --> 15:39.396
Next time you tell the cops
you don't recognize anyone.

15:39.480 --> 15:41.065
-Use your head.
-You know what?

15:41.148 --> 15:44.485
Next time I'll be sitting at home
swiping left on your calls from county.

15:44.568 --> 15:46.987
-You'll be swiping left on my calls…
-This is not…

15:47.988 --> 15:49.823
I can't fucking stand you, Bob.

15:51.909 --> 15:53.035
Come here.

15:58.791 --> 16:00.834
Give me a sec to have
a chinwag with these blokes.

16:01.502 --> 16:02.670
-Are you…
-A second.

16:04.463 --> 16:06.131
-Motherfucker. Yeah.
-I love you!

16:11.595 --> 16:12.680
Hey, Judy.

16:13.639 --> 16:14.556
Stan.

16:16.684 --> 16:17.601
You look amazing.

16:18.978 --> 16:19.812
You…

16:20.854 --> 16:23.816
Earring? It works.

16:26.777 --> 16:28.612
-It's been a while, huh?
-Yeah.

16:31.281 --> 16:33.492
I didn't want to leave things
the way we did…

16:33.575 --> 16:35.244
-It's okay.
-It's just that he…

16:35.327 --> 16:36.161
Really.

16:36.912 --> 16:39.123
-Uh…
-I mean, for a while, it was…

16:40.374 --> 16:42.668
But now it's just so good to see you.

16:42.751 --> 16:44.003
Wowee.

16:45.671 --> 16:47.339
Look who it is, eh?

16:48.173 --> 16:49.758
What a lovely surprise.

16:50.467 --> 16:52.052
Look, it's our old buddy, Stan.

16:52.136 --> 16:53.721
-Hey, Bob.
-Hey!

16:53.804 --> 16:55.681
Did you know Stan was gonna be here?

16:55.764 --> 16:56.890
-I didn't know…
-She didn't.

16:56.974 --> 16:57.808
She didn't know.

16:57.891 --> 17:01.520
This is such a fun surprise
to have you here, mate. Eh?

17:01.603 --> 17:03.856
Especially after that conversation we had.

17:04.565 --> 17:07.609
You remember the one.
Where you should just stay in New York.

17:07.693 --> 17:10.654
And yet, here you are. Huh? What a treat.

17:10.738 --> 17:15.034
In Philly. In our town. My town.

17:15.117 --> 17:16.952
Okay. Yeah. What are you doing here?

17:17.036 --> 17:18.787
I got a guy who wants to see you.

17:19.580 --> 17:20.664
Do I know him?

17:21.874 --> 17:23.625
No, but you're going to want to.

17:30.424 --> 17:32.217
Sure, come along too, Bob.

17:34.678 --> 17:36.096
Dumb motherfucker.

17:42.269 --> 17:44.855
Way I figure it,
we'll need some lock burnouts.

17:45.689 --> 17:47.316
Maybe some gas for the guards.

17:47.399 --> 17:49.818
I've been playing
with some fentanyl derivatives.

17:52.029 --> 17:54.907
-What's the split?
-Even-steven, across the board.

17:54.990 --> 17:55.908
What about Bob?

17:57.201 --> 17:58.035
What about Bob?

17:59.244 --> 18:00.245
What can I get you?

18:00.329 --> 18:04.124
Oh, hey, Jenna. I actually had a question
about the pork chop.

18:04.208 --> 18:07.461
-Is it grass-fed or Niman Ranch--
-He'll have a burger. Same here.

18:08.587 --> 18:10.380
-No, I'm good.
-You're not gonna eat?

18:10.464 --> 18:12.341
-I don't eat lunch.
-What do you mean?

18:12.424 --> 18:13.634
One meal a day, mate.

18:14.593 --> 18:17.096
Keeps me sharp, you know, focused.

18:17.888 --> 18:19.723
Rockets up the testosterone, too.

18:20.390 --> 18:22.518
Well, today's meal is fucking lunch.

18:23.477 --> 18:25.062
Burgers, all around.

18:28.524 --> 18:31.360
Look, we're a package deal,
me and the wifey here, yeah?

18:31.443 --> 18:34.488
But you're in luck. Safes are my thing.
So, tell 'em, babe.

18:35.989 --> 18:37.074
He's very good.

18:37.157 --> 18:40.077
Thank you. But we're all set.
Leo's on safes.

18:40.160 --> 18:41.411
Who, Shamrock Shake?

18:41.954 --> 18:45.082
No offense, mate,
but, uh, would you hire you for this job?

18:45.165 --> 18:46.416
You have no fucking--

18:46.500 --> 18:49.294
That's going to be two shares.
One for her, one for me.

18:49.378 --> 18:51.964
None of this
community property bullshit, okay?

18:52.047 --> 18:54.091
Do your job, you'll get your cut.

18:55.551 --> 18:57.970
What about seed cash?
I'm going to need gear.

18:58.053 --> 19:00.848
Credit card skim I could set up.
Get us a pretty decent score.

19:00.931 --> 19:03.183
I got an OTB job set up for seed.

19:04.893 --> 19:06.478
How do we know you can pull this off?

19:06.562 --> 19:09.189
You don't. So you can stay here in Philly,

19:09.273 --> 19:11.441
pulling off dime jobs
and bailing out this asshole…

19:11.525 --> 19:12.651
Alleged asshole.

19:12.734 --> 19:16.405
…or take a long shot
that puts you on top for good.

19:22.161 --> 19:27.457
So this vault, you say there's biometrics,
uninterruptible power supplies…

19:27.541 --> 19:30.711
And ten other things that
we don't know about. It's a nightmare.

19:30.794 --> 19:32.671
Hell of a sales job, Leo.

19:34.464 --> 19:38.552
But ask yourself, how do I know
the things I do already know?

19:41.597 --> 19:42.931
You've got eyes inside.

19:48.478 --> 19:50.814
Someone
punched through our firewall.

19:50.898 --> 19:53.942
They used an app-suite whitelist
to gain access.

19:54.026 --> 19:55.444
I mean, smart, really.

19:56.528 --> 19:58.405
Could be a grey hat doing it for fun.

19:58.488 --> 20:00.824
Or The Triplets testing our system.

20:00.908 --> 20:03.911
I shuttered the ports
and set alerts in case they try again,

20:03.994 --> 20:06.288
and I'll let you know if anything pops up.

20:06.371 --> 20:09.249
Okay. No time's too late. And good work.

20:09.333 --> 20:10.292
Thank you.

20:10.375 --> 20:14.838
And, uh, that Junior VP position…

20:14.922 --> 20:18.675
We'll have a decision soon enough.
You just keep doing what you're doing.

20:19.259 --> 20:20.093
Okay.

20:25.474 --> 20:27.100
We have eyes on Andrew?

20:27.184 --> 20:29.436
We don't. But we can.

20:36.568 --> 20:38.987
It's not stress, because I'm not stressed.

20:39.071 --> 20:39.947
Clearly.

20:40.030 --> 20:41.448
There's just a lot going on.

